                <head>No. 108.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Earl <persName type="from">Granville</persName> to Lord
                            <persName type="to">Tenterden</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign Office</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-06-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 12, 1872</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">[From British Blue Book “North America,” No. 10, (1872,) p. 2.]</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: If any circumstances not provided for should
                    occur while you are endeavoring to obtain an adjournment according to your
                    instructions, you will telegraph the particulars to me and ask for
                    instructions.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GRANVILLE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
